<section id="fs-idm199510992">
<title>Historical Reasoning Questions</title>
<para id="fs-idm168050176">I have often been utterly astonished, since I came to the north, to find persons who could speak of the singing, among slaves, as evidence of their contentment and happiness. It is impossible to conceive of a greater mistake. Slaves sing most when they are most unhappy. The songs of the slave represent the sorrows of his heart; and he is relieved by them, only as an aching heart is relieved by its tears….</para>
<para id="fs-idm169369232" class="right">—Frederick Douglass, <emphasis effect="italics">Narrative of the Life of Frederick Douglass</emphasis>, 1845</para>
<exercise id="fs-idm214759472">
